================================================================================
  7. MOTION
================================================================================

  --pt-ease-standard     cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0, 1)    slight overshoot in, hard stop out
  --pt-ease-emphasized   cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0, 1.2)
  --pt-dur-snap          120ms   Press feedback (translateY(1px) on :active)
  --pt-dur-fast          180ms   Hover, color transitions
  --pt-dur-base          220ms   Sheet entry, menu reveal
  --pt-dur-slow          320ms
  --pt-dur-pulse        1800ms   ONLY for live-verified status dot

RULES
  - No bouncy springs. No "fun" wiggle.
  - Animations confirm — they never entertain.
  - No loading spinner > 1s without a skeleton state.
  - The 1800ms pulse is the ONLY animation that exceeds 1s, and it only ever
    applies to the live-verified status dot. The pulse IS the message.


================================================================================
  8. ICONOGRAPHY
================================================================================

Geometric line icons in Lucide style.

  - 24×24 viewBox
  - 2px stroke
  - fill: none, stroke: currentColor
  - Round caps and joins
  - No filled icons. No bicolor. No emoji.

Starter sprite at assets/icons.svg (~40 glyphs): shield-check, qr-code,
wallet, share, settings, user, bell, check, x, alert-triangle, info,
chevron-left/right/down, arrow-right, plus, search, copy, eye, clock,
calendar, map-pin, mail, phone, log-out, camera, refresh, upload, lock,
zap, building, briefcase, users, more-horizontal, home, globe, star,
download, external-link, badge-check.

USAGE
  <svg width="20" height="20" style="color: var(--pt-verified-700)">
    <use href="assets/icons.svg#badge-check" />
  </svg>

WHERE ICONS GO
  - Inside buttons (16–18px), leading element, 6–8px gap to label
  - Settings/list rows (18px) inside a 32×32 paper-100 rounded square
  - Status markers near the live-pulse — but NEVER both `Icon` and
    `pt-live-dot` in the same group; pick one.
  - Activity timeline nodes

WHERE ICONS DON'T GO
  - Decorative header marks
  - As bullet glyphs in body text
  - Inside the Pass card itself (the Pass is type-only by design)
  - Combined into "icon stack" compositions

EMOJI / UNICODE
  - Not in product UI.
  - `✓` and `→` permitted in marketing email subjects, sparingly.
  - `·` (U+00B7) is the canonical metadata separator.


